    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The process of forming a whole from various parts, particularly the formation of a compound material by the combination of its elements or constituents, of the production of white or other compound light by the combination of its constituent colors, or of the production of a complex musical sound by the combination of its component simple tones. In philosophy, it is the action of proceeding in thought from causes to effects, or from laws or principles to their consequences.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>各個不同部分形成一個整體的過程，特別是藉由結合其元素或成分形成複合材料、藉由結合其組成色彩產生白色或其他複合光、或藉由結合其組成單音產生複合樂音。在哲學領域中，則是指自因至果、或自法律、原則至其推論的思維活動。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het vormen van een geheel uit verschillende delen, met name het vormen van een samengesteld materiaal door de combinatie van elementen of onderdelen, van de productie van wit of ander samengesteld licht door de combinatie van de samenstellende kleuren, of van de productie van een complex muzikaal geluid door de combinatie van eenvoudige tonen. In de filosofie is dit in het denken overgaan van oorzaken naar gevolgen, of van wetten of uitgangspunten naar de consequenties.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
